BallandSocket Joints
Ballandsocket joints possess a rounded balllike end of one bone fitting into a cuplike socket of another
bone This organization allows the greatest range of motion as all movement types are possible in all directions
Examples of ballandsocket joints are the shoulder and hip joints Figure 3832
Figure 3832 The shoulder joint is an example of a ballandsocket joint
